title: ICE: non_lifetime_binders `unexpected bound ty in binder: BoundTy {...}`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(non_lifetime_binders)] fn main() { for
|| -> & main {}; } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.69.0-nightly (f4f5fc3e5 2023-02-17) binary: rustc commit-hash: f4f5fc3e5cc70b7a43bf7b518c455f3d9bada9e3 commit-date: 2023-02-17 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.69.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.7 ``` ### Error output ``` error[E0637]: `&` without an explicit lifetime name cannot be used here --> 2f364877ae32a51855925609c897ffa9f739c835.rs:2:21 | 2 | for
|| -> & main {}; | ^ explicit lifetime name needed here error[E0658]: `for<...>` binders for closures are experimental --> 2f364877ae32a51855925609c897ffa9f739c835.rs:2:5 | 2 | for
|| -> & main {}; | ^^^^^^^^^ | = note: see issue #97362 for more information = help: add `#![feature(closure_lifetime_binder)]` to the crate attributes to enable = help: consider removing `for<...>` warning: the feature `non_lifetime_binders` is incomplete and may not be safe to use and/or cause compiler crashes --> :1:9 | 1 | feature(non_lifetime_binders) | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ | = note: see issue #1 for more information = note: `#[warn(incomplete_features)]` on by default warning: type parameter `main` should have an upper camel case name --> 2f364877ae32a51855925609c897ffa9f739c835.rs:2:9 | 2 | for
|| -> & main {}; | ^^^^ help: convert the identifier to upper camel case: `Main` | = note: `#[warn(non_camel_case_types)]` on by default ```
